INSERT INTO `tb_sights` VALUES (39,17,5,'Bibixonim',7,30,'Самарканд, улица Шахи Зинда, 185','39.66265651090272,66.98796562003629',2000,3000,'Ularning eng qadimiysi Qusam ibn Abbos maqbarasi boʻlib, xalq orasida Shohizinda (tirik shoh) nomi bilan mashhur. Ansambl bir-biri bilan yoʻlak orqali bogʻlangan 3 guruh binolardan iborat. Quyi guruhdagi inshootlar Ulugʻbek oʻgʻli nomidan qurdirgan Abdulaziz chortogʻi (1434—35), unga shim.dan Davlat qushbegi madrasasi (1812—13) tutash, uning qarshisidagi ayvonli masjid naqshlar bilan nafis bezatilgan. 40 bosqichli tik zinapoya oʻrtaligʻining chap tomonida ziyoratxona va goʻrxonadan iborat qoʻshgumbazli maqbara (15-asr) joylashgan.','Shah-i-Zinda is a stunning complex of mausoleums in Samarkand, Uzbekistan, dating back to the 9th–14th centuries. Known for its vibrant blue tiles and intricate Islamic architecture, it is considered one of the most sacred sites in Central Asia and a masterpiece of Timurid craftsmanship. The name means \"The Living King,\" referring to Kusam ibn Abbas, a cousin of the Prophet Muhammad, who is believed to be buried there.','active','images/permanent/image-81YGE22BX4.png,images/permanent/image-tlp1TkI5lb.png,images/permanent/image-986GbJpvPh.png','2025-05-24','2025-05-24 10:33:24',NULL,NULL,30,NULL,1,NULL,21,1,'{\"wc\": true, \"wifi\": true}',NULL,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,NULL),(40,17,5,'Ulug\'bek abservatoriyasi',7,30,'Самарканд, 3-й проезд Ислама Каримова, 90','39.6748551501508,67.0058247475744',3000,5000,'Ulugʻbek rasadxonasi – Samarqanddagi 15-asr meʼmorchiligining nodir namunalaridan biri, koʻhna astronomik kuzatuv muassasasi. 1420-yillarda temuriylar davri astronomi Ulugʻbek tomonidan barpo etilgan. Rasadxonada Al-Koshiy, Ali Qushchi va Ulugʻbek kabi musulmon astronomlar ishlagan. Rasadxona 1449-yilda vayron qilingan va 1908-yilda qayta kashf etilgan','Ulughbek Observatory in Samarkand, Uzbekistan, is one of the most significant astronomical centers of the medieval world. Built in the 15th century by the Timurid ruler and astronomer Ulughbek, it housed a massive sextant for observing stars. The observatory played a key role in advancing astronomy and produced remarkably accurate star charts long before modern technology.','active','images/permanent/image-3RdTx5mOsJ.png,images/permanent/image-uoxNRNKF3N.png,images/permanent/image-Qkxb0EVYkz.png,images/permanent/image-4sqD9edwpt.png,images/permanent/image-k1Bj4Xadml.png','2025-05-24','2025-05-24 10:40:31',NULL,NULL,30,NULL,1,NULL,21,1,'{\"wc\": false, \"wifi\": true}',NULL,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,NULL),(41,17,5,'Congress center',7,30,'Rowing canal, Konigil massif, Samarkand, 140319, Uzbekistan\n','41.297035695878684,69.26002616938129',500,1200,'The Silk Road Samarkand touristic complex provides a spacious congress center with a total area of more than 28,000 m2. This is a building decorated in the oriental style with large panoramic windows. Its high-tech venue equipped with modern hardware is designed for hosting congresses, conferences, symposiums, exhibitions, presentations, shows, and banquets.','Silk Road Tour Complex is a modern tourist hub in Samarkand, Uzbekistan, designed to showcase the rich heritage of the ancient Silk Road. Located near major historical landmarks, it offers cultural experiences, traditional crafts, cuisine, and guided tours that reflect the vibrant history of trade and cultural exchange along this legendary route.','active','images/permanent/image-i1TYtpaX0d.png,images/permanent/image-zv7MRluR2P.png,images/permanent/image-OzlRSVskUC.png,images/permanent/image-rEWyUaKo9w.png,images/permanent/image-sb7qugUSOy.png,images/permanent/image-yYgabJ6tma.png,images/permanent/image-8QQtQzj37Q.png,images/permanent/image-bm8vzOiX7u.png','2025-05-24','2025-05-24 12:04:45','08:00:00','21:00:00',30,NULL,1,NULL,21,1,'{\"wc\": true, \"wifi\": true}',NULL,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,NULL),(44,17,5,'Registan',7,30,'Самарканд, Регистанская улица, 135','39.65468110928221,66.97578369268608',1000,5000,'<p><strong>Dastlabki 1417–1420-yillarda Ulugʻbek madrasasi bunyod etilib, keyinchalik qarshisiga – maydonning sharqiy qismida Ulugʻbek xonaqosi (1424-yil), shimoliy qismiga Mirzoyi karvonsaroyi, janubiga Alika Koʻkaldosh juma masjidi (1430-yil) bunyod etilgan, yonida esa yogʻochdan xotamkori uslubida Masjidi Muqatta va Abusaid madrasasi qurilgan. 1420–1440-yillarida Registon hashamatli meʼmoriy ansamblga aylangan. XVII asrda Samarqand hokimi Yalangtoʻsh Bahodir vayrona holatdagi Ulugʻbek xonaqosi oʻrniga Sherdor madrasasini (1619–1636), Mirzoyi karvonsaroyi oʻrniga Tillakori masjidini (1646–1660) qurdirgan. Registon maydoni oʻzining rang-barang koshinkori bezaklari; naqshinkori peshtoqlari, ulkan gumbazlari bilan Markaziy Osiyo meʼmorchligining noyob yodgorligi hisoblanadi.</strong></p>',NULL,'active','/images/permanent/image-A00eRSjjXg.png,/images/permanent/image-o4aupkaV8i.png,/images/permanent/image-PuPJ7YJpWc.png,/images/permanent/image-PtlbASTwqH.png,/images/permanent/image-3jowb6yylX.png','2025-05-27','2025-05-27 07:04:06','00:00:00','23:59:59',18,NULL,1,'{\"all_days_open\": true}',21,1,'{\"wc\": true, \"wifi\": true}','{\"other\": true, \"passport\": true}',NULL,0.00,0,NULL,NULL),(45,17,5,'Imom al-Buxoriy majmuasi',7,30,'Самарканд, Регистанская улица, 135','39.65461061961983,66.97581253173051',1000,5000,'<p>Imom al-Buxoriy majmuasi Imom al-Buxoriy majmuasi – bu yirik islom olimi, hadis ilmining asoschilaridan biri bo‘lgan Imom Muhammad al-Buxoriy (rahmatullohi alayh) qabrini o‘z ichiga olgan muqaddas ziyoratgohdir. Manzil: Samarkand shahridan taxminan 25 km uzoqlikda, Hartang qishlog‘ida joylashgan. Majmua tarkibi: Ziyoratgoh (maqbara) – Imom al-Buxoriy qabr joylashgan joy. Masjid – Zamonaviy uslubda qurilgan, katta jamoaviy namoz o‘qish imkoniyati mavjud. Kutubxona va muzey – Islomiy manbalar, Qur’oni Karim qo‘lyozmalari va tarixiy eksponatlar mavjud. Hovli va ayvonlar – Ziyoratchilar uchun qulay muhit va dam olish maskani. Qisqacha ma’lumot: Imom al-Buxoriy eng mashhur islomiy hadis to‘plami – “Al-Jome’ as-Sahih” asari muallifi bo‘lib, u musulmon olamida ikkinchi eng muqaddas kitob hisoblanadi (Qur’oni Karimdan keyin).</p>',NULL,'active','/images/permanent/image-qx8lCkOTQL.png,/images/permanent/image-lL7Bu8LABY.png,/images/permanent/image-lDagpqprKE.png,/images/permanent/image-5vb09wEz6M.png,/images/permanent/image-0kFuYDve8j.png,/images/permanent/image-xe7KAd3npO.png','2025-05-27','2025-05-27 07:34:36','00:00:00','23:59:59',25,NULL,1,'{\"all_days_open\": true}',21,1,'{\"wc\": true, \"wifi\": false}','{\"other\": true, \"passport\": true}',NULL,0.00,0,NULL,NULL),(74,17,2,'Shohizinda',7,30,'Самарканд, Регистанская улица, 135','39.65482402924839,66.97577439576064',1000,5000,'<p>Samarkand [1] It is the second-largest city in Uzbekistan and the capital of Samarqand Province. The city is on the old Silk Road between China and the West, and is an Islamic centre for scholarly study. In the 14th century, it became the capital of the empire of Timur (Tamerlane), and is the site of his mausoleum, the Gur-e Amir. The Bibi-Khanym Mosque remains one of the city\'s most famous landmarks. The Registan was the ancient centre of the city.</p>',NULL,'active','/images/permanent/image-9zZoQtrjg6.png,/images/permanent/image-wAg5nZVog1.png,/images/permanent/image-rWhNJlK8CU.png,/images/permanent/image-zeaEGWh3i8.png,/images/permanent/image-x7cmUTQ0qR.png,/images/permanent/image-zeApyNoLZC.png,/images/permanent/image-G6wnbgCeq0.png','2025-07-24','2025-07-24 12:31:41','06:00:00','23:00:00',30,15,1,'{\"1\": {\"open\": \"06:00\", \"close\": \"23:00\", \"enabled\": true}, \"3\": {\"open\": \"09:10\", \"close\": \"22:00\", \"enabled\": true}, \"4\": {\"open\": \"10:00\", \"close\": \"19:00\", \"enabled\": true}}',31,0,'{\"wc\": true, \"wifi\": false}','{\"other\": true, \"passport\": true}','<p>rules and policy here will be</p>',0.00,0,'refundable',10.00),(79,17,2,'Gur Amir maqbarasi – Samarqand durdonasi',7,68,'Uzbekistan, Samarkand, Oqsaroy koʻchasi, 1','39.64849442662273,66.9691913144',5000,10000,'<p><strong>Gur Amir maqbarasi – Samarqand durdonasi</strong></p><p>Gur Amir maqbarasi – buyuk sarkarda va saltanat asoschisi Amir Temurning qabri joylashgan muqaddas maskan bo‘lib, O‘zbekistonning Samarqand shahrida joylashgan. “Gur Amir” so‘zi fors tilidan tarjima qilinganda “Amirning qabridir” degan ma’noni anglatadi. Bu maqbara XIV asr oxirida Amir Temurning buyrug‘i bilan qurilgan bo‘lib, dastlab uning nabirasi Muhammad Sulton uchun mo‘ljallangan edi. Biroq keyinchalik Temurning o‘zi, nabirasi Ulug‘bek, o‘g‘li Shohruh va boshqa yaqin qarindoshlari ham shu yerga dafn etilgan.</p><p>Gur Amir maqbarasi Markaziy Osiyo me’morchiligining eng go‘zal namunasidir. Uning osmon rangdagi gumbazi, nafis koshinlar bilan bezatilgan devorlari va o‘ymakor naqshlari mehmonlarni hayratga soladi. Bu maqbara nafaqat tarixiy yodgorlik, balki Temuriylar davrining madaniy va san’at merosini ifodalovchi muhim obidadir. Har yili minglab sayyohlar bu yerga tashrif buyurib, buyuk bobokalonimizning xotirasiga hurmat bajo keltiradilar. Gur Amir – o‘zbek tarixining faxri va jahon miqyosidagi bebaho me’moriy yodgorlikdir.</p>',NULL,'active','images/permanent/image-LDMbD8hTrF.png,images/permanent/image-9vrfib6JQy.png,images/permanent/image-h2JFk7uvAo.png,images/permanent/image-4DPuM7sUlT.png,images/permanent/image-lZ3ojVbURO.png,images/permanent/image-9rmTirB8Op.png,images/permanent/image-LNgVqTnYq8.png','2025-07-25','2025-07-25 12:18:34',NULL,NULL,30,30,1,'{\"1\": {\"open\": \"07:00\", \"close\": \"21:00\", \"enabled\": true}, \"2\": {\"open\": \"07:00\", \"close\": \"21:00\", \"enabled\": true}, \"3\": {\"open\": \"07:00\", \"close\": \"21:00\", \"enabled\": true}, \"4\": {\"open\": \"07:00\", \"close\": \"21:00\", \"enabled\": true}, \"5\": {\"open\": \"07:00\", \"close\": \"21:00\", \"enabled\": true}, \"6\": {\"open\": \"07:00\", \"close\": \"21:00\", \"enabled\": true}, \"7\": {\"open\": \"07:00\", \"close\": \"21:00\", \"enabled\": true}}',31,1,'{\"wc\": true, \"wifi\": false}','{\"other\": true, \"passport\": true}','<h3><strong>Tashrif Siyosati – Gur Amir Maqbarasi</strong></h3><p><strong>Ish vaqti:</strong><br>Maqbara har kuni soat <strong>07:00 dan 19:00 gacha</strong> ochiq.</p><p><strong>Kirish chiptasi:</strong></p><p>Mahalliy fuqarolar uchun chegirmali narxlar mavjud.</p><p>Chet ellik sayyohlar uchun alohida tarif qo‘llaniladi.</p><p>Talabalar va pensionerlar tegishli hujjat bilan chegirmadan foydalanishlari mumkin.</p><p><strong>Fotosurat va video olish:</strong></p><p>Tashqi hududda suratga olish bepul.</p><p>Ichki qismda professional video yoki fotosurat olish uchun maxsus ruxsatnoma talab qilinadi.</p><p><strong>Hurmat qoidalari:</strong></p><p>Qabr atrofi va maqbara ichida ovozni balandlatmaslik.</p><p>Diniy va madaniy qadriyatlarga hurmat bilan yondashish.</p><p>Axlat tashlash, devorlarni ushlash yoki zarar yetkazish taqiqlanadi.</p><p><strong>Gid xizmatlari:</strong></p><p>Sayyohlar uchun tajribali gidlar xizmat ko‘rsatadi (o‘zbek, rus va ingliz tillarida).</p>',0.00,0,'non_refundable',0.00);
